posts.name: Angel Falls Coffee Company
posts.note: Angel Falls Coffee Company is a coffeehouse offering carefully sourced java and tea, plus baked goods and a full lunch menu most days. I ordered their large hot chocolate with whipped cream all for $2.08 with tax. Such a steal. While sitting here, catching up on e-mail, I heard one of the workers tell a customer they had 50 hot teas and three cold teas.

posts.name: Big Al's Diner
posts.note: Big Al's Diner is a compact diner is dishing up generous portions of breakfast all day and hearty American fare at lunch. When I was at Big Al's Diner, I ordered the cheese omelette with rye toast and corned beef hash. It was a huge plate of food.
posts.cptn: Cheese omelette, rye toast, and corned beef hash at Big Al's Diner in Cleveland, Ohio

posts.name: Crave
posts.note: Crave serves a diverse menu with global influences is presented in a colorful, contemporary, art-filled setting.

posts.name: Crop Bistro & Bar
posts.note: Crop Bistro and Bar is a bank turned sleek, upscale New American eatery with a chef's table and a focus on local ingredients.

posts.name: Downtown 140
posts.note: Downtown 140 is an adventurous New American dishes are presented in a romantic, subterranean, brick-walled setting. If they have it on special order the sea bass wrapped in prosciutto with clam broth, wild mushrooms, and fennel salad or the pork charcuterie board or the escargot covered in puff pastry to seal in the garlic and cream sauce. NOTE: Restaurant is downstairs.

posts.name: The Eye Opener
posts.note: The Eye Opener is a warm and comfortable diner serving classic American breakfast, omelettes, and specialty sandwiches. You should order their home-made breakfast sausages with your breakfast. It's not loud so you can have a nice conversation with others and not have to strain to hear.

posts.name: Findlay Market
posts.note: Findlay Market is a longtime hub of vendors selling meat, produce, and other local foods, plus a seasonal farmers' market.

posts.name: Frank's Bratwurst
posts.note: Frank's Bratwurst has been serving bratwurst that is like no other, derived from a secret recipe that has gone through rigorous research and development. Franks' Bratwurst makes some of the best bratwurst sandwiches and other sausages too. You need to order a few different kinds with friends so you can try them all.

posts.name: Ghostlight Coffee (Historic South Park)
posts.note: Ghostlight Coffee (Historic South Park) serves espresso drinks and pastries are served at this relaxed coffee shop with high ceilings and brick walls. From their website, 'Established in 2011, Ghostlight Coffee has become a favorite place for Daytonians to meet...from hosting political round tables to helping set up secret proposals; you never know what will happen next or who you will run into at Ghostlight! We also host a monthly featured coffee roaster, which we brew to order by the cup in a Chemex on our Curtis Gold Cup coffee brewer. Some of the amazing coffee roasters that we have had the honor to feature include Onyx Coffee Lab, Brandywine Coffee Roasters, Pettibone Coffee, Blueprint Coffee, and many others. Our baked goods are handmade for each cup! We are a coffeehouse and bakery, with two amazing bakers putting love and creativity into every item. Our bakers are known for inventing new and flavorful goods like muffins, bagels, scones, breakfast sandwiches, cookies, biscotti, and more each day.' NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: Great Lakes Brewing Company
posts.note: Great Lakes Brewing Company is an iconic microbrewery with house suds, an updated American menu, free tours and a patio.

posts.name: The Greenhouse Tavern
posts.note: The Greenhouse Tavern is a hip haunt with locally driven New American fare, a rooftop patio, and creative cocktails.

posts.name: Happy Dog East
posts.note: Happy Dog East serves quarter-pound hot dogs with creative toppings plus live music and 75+ tap beers in a convivial space. NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: Hot Sauce Williams
posts.note: Hot Sauce Williams is a family-friendly barbecue joint is known for its Polish Boy sandwich, fried chicken and mac 'n' cheese.

posts.name: Le Bistro Du Beaujolais
posts.note: Le Bistro Du Beaujolais is a quaint French bistro in a circa-1830 home with patio seats, fixed-price options, and French-only wines.

posts.name: Le Petit Triangle Café
posts.note: Le Petit Triangle Café is a Parisian offering for morning coffee and pastries, along with casual midday meals and evening wine dinners. I ordered a great croissant ham, egg, and cheese breakfast sandwich. My friend ordered the escargots with parsley-garlic butter and sliced baguette.

posts.name: LJ Shanghai
posts.note: From the Cleveland Eater website about LJ Shanghai, 'Cleveland has a surprisingly robust Asiatown neighborhood, and one of the buzziest new entries is LJ Shanghai, an approachable Chinese noodle house. Initially, it was the xiao long bao or soup dumplings that got folks in the door. But once seated, they eagerly branched out to the spicy beef noodle soup, Shanghai-style scallion noodles, preserved vegetable and pork soup, and soy sauce duck. A glassed-off kitchen allows diners to observe the deft dumpling construction, which is nearly continuous given the rate at which they are depleted.'
posts.rcmmnd: Best Chinese restaurant in every state from MSN website

posts.name: Lola Bistro
posts.note: Michael Symon's Lola Bistro serves New American eatery serves rustic fare in a sleek, bustling setting.

posts.name: Mitchell's Ice Cream
posts.note: Each batch of Mitchell's Ice Cream is hand-crafted in our Ohio City Kitchen (watch them anytime). Ingredients that grow well in our Ohio climate they get from friends around here. Ingredients that grow best in different climates they get from the world's best producers. They do a lot of searching, and they're never be done.

posts.name: The Mustard Seed Market and Cafe
posts.note: The Mustard Seed Market and Cafe is Akron’s original healthy restaurant that features all natural and organic ingredients, made fresh to order and served with a smile! Our forward-thinking menu offers a wide variety of Gluten Free friendly, Hormone and Anti-biotic free Meats, Vegetarian, Vegan and Allergen-Friendly cuisine inspired from around the world. We ordered the Buffalo cauliflower which is lightly battered cauliflower fried and covered in spicy sauce served with a side or two of blue cheese dressing.  You should also order one of their bowls that have chopped mixed veggies, nuts, meat if you want. You can create and combine what you want.

posts.name: Nervous Dog Coffee Bar
posts.note: Nervous Dog Coffee Bar is a relaxed coffeehouse serving hot drinks and sandwiches in a casual, quirky atmosphere. It's a great little place to relax, read, and get some work done with comfortable seating.

posts.name: O'Neil House Bed and Breakfast
posts.note: The O’Neil House Bed and Breakfast is one of Akron's unique jewels. Located in the heart of West Akron at the major intersection of West Exchange Street and Mull Avenue, the 19-room Tudor mansion is an architectural treasure sitting on six parcels of park-like land. They serve a wonderful breakfast with fresh fruits, a pastry, and an omelette. The room I stayed in has chairs in it but also had another sitting room with a sofa, table and two chairs, a small TV and two walls of windows.

posts.name: Pho Lang Thang
posts.note: noPho Lang Thang is an upbeat Vietnamese joint inside Findlay Market for bowls of pho and banh mi sandwiches. You should order their Pho along with the head cheese banh mi.

posts.name: Sokolowski's University Inn
posts.note: Sokolowski's University Inn is a family-owned landmark serves cafeteria-style Polish classics in homey surroundings.

posts.name: Steve's Gyro's
posts.note: If you’re craving a gyro, Steve's Gyro's asks that you arrive early. Steve's Gyro's do sell out early every day, and because of that, they do close earlier than scheduled Market hours. I liked it so much I went back the next day to get one to have for lunch for the road trip home to DC.

posts.name: Slyman's Restaurant
posts.note: Slyman's Restaurant is a retro breakfast and lunch deli known for corned beef sandwiches served in simple diner digs.

posts.name: Taste of Belgium - Over The Rhine
posts.note: Taste of Belgium - Over The Rhine is a chic spot offering Belgian-tinged dishes alongside a long beer list along with wine and cocktails. Make sure you order the waffle, chicken, and waffle, or the traditional stew made with beer-braised beef. From the Food Network website, 'This spot serves Belgian classics that Guy finds irresistible. He declares the dense Belgian waffle to be “outstanding” and also digs the Belgian pretzel with a side of beer cheese. If you are in the mood for something heartier, try the Carbonnades — a traditional stew made with beer-braised beef.'

posts.name: Tony Packo's Restaurant
posts.note: Tony Packo's Restaurant is a casual, long-running Hungarian-American spot with signature hot dogs, soups, and classic entrees. The restaurant became famous when it was mentioned in several M*A*S*H episodes and is noted for its signature sandwich. NOTE: They have multiple locations.

posts.name: TownHall
posts.note: TownHall is a locally sourced and innovative bar bites, and vegan options served in a contemporary setting with patio. TownHall is located about a block or so from the Westside Market.

posts.name: West Side Market
posts.note: West Side Market is a grand, bustling public market from 1912 featuring vendors for meat, produce, bread and hot food.

posts.name: West Side Market Cafe
posts.note: The West Side Market Cafe is a casual eatery in the historic market, dishing up down-home American eats for breakfast and lunch. I ended up ordering an omelette with home fries, rye toast, and a side sausage.
